==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Pluralism
<hw>Plu"ral*ism</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The
quality or state of being plural, or in the plural number.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Eccl.)</fld> <def>The state of a pluralist; the
holding of more than one ecclesiastical living at a time.</def>
<mark>[Eng.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Pluralist</ent>⟦br⟧
